1802482.text: There are three types of Card Pools in game: Soul Summon, Awakening Summon and Dreamland Summon.$B$Soul Summon: Permanent Card Pool with no Rate-up Dolls;$B$Awakening Summon: Open when there is no event. Has Rate-up Doll;$B$Dreamland Summon: Open during events. Has Rate-up Doll.$B$<color=#ffca65>During event time, Awakening Summon will be closed and reopens once the event ends and the guarantee summon count will carry over from the previous Awakening Summon Card Pool.$B$During non-event time, Dreamland Summon will be closed and reopens when the next event starts and the guarantee summon count will carry over from the previous Dreamland Summon Card Pool.</color>

1802480.text: A Rate-up Doll is guaranteed to drop from Awakening Summon Card Pool within 160 summons.$B$After getting a Rate-up Doll, the count will be reset and "Guaranteed Rate-up Doll within 160 summons" will be once again displayed in the bottom left corner.

1802478.text: A UR Doll is guaranteed to drop from Awakening Summon Card Pool within 80 summons.$B$After getting a UR Doll, the count will be reset and "Guaranteed UR within 80 summons" will be once again displayed in the bottom left corner.

1802474.text: Dreamland Summon's guarantee summon count is not shared with Soul Summon or Awakening Summon, and the count is carried over independently.$B$Example: A player tried 40 summons from the Dreamland Summon between 10:00 on July 22th and 3:59 on July 29th, but did not get a Rate-up Doll. This means there are still 120 summons left in the guarantee.$B$The next time a new Dreamland Summon Card Pool opens, the 120 remaining summons from the guarantee will carry over until the player gets a Rate-up doll.

1802472.text: The Rate-up Doll is guaranteed to drop from Dreamland Summon Card Pool within 160 summons.$B$After getting a Rate-up Doll, the count will be reset and "Guaranteed Rate-up Doll within 160 summons" will be once again displayed in the bottom left corner.
